<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="747" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="747">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="747">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1949" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Acanthobrama" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acanthobrama orontis" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="orontis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="747">Acanthobrama orontis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified by Berg (1949) in Lake Amik (Orontes) in Turkey. 
<bibRefCitation author="Goren, M" journalOrPublisher="Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" pagination="291 - 315" refId="B22" refString="Goren, M, Fishelson, L, Trewavas, E, 1973. The cyprinid fishes of Acanthobrama Heckel and related genera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Zoology 24: 291 - 315" title="The cyprinid fishes of Acanthobrama Heckel and related genera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." volume="24" year="1973">Goren et al. (1973)</bibRefCitation>
reported it to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. marmid" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" rank="species" species="marmid">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="747">A. marmid</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Krupp, F" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" refId="B29" refString="Krupp, F, 1985. Systematik und Zoogeographie der Suesswasserfische des levantinischen Grabenbruch-systems und der Ostkueste des Mittelmeers. Dissertation, Johannes Gutenberg Universitaet, Mainz 215 pp." title="Systematik und Zoogeographie der Suesswasserfische des levantinischen Grabenbruch-systems und der Ostkueste des Mittelmeers. Dissertation, Johannes Gutenberg Universitaet, Mainz 215 pp." year="1985">Krupp (1985)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogutskaya, NG" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" pagination="161 - 186" refId="B8" refString="Bogutskaya, NG, 1997. Contribution to the knowledge of leuciscine fishes of Asia Minor. Part 2. An annotated checklist of leuciscine fishes (Leuciscinae, Cyprinidae) of Turkey with descriptions of a new species and two new subspecies. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut 94: 161 - 186" title="Contribution to the knowledge of leuciscine fishes of Asia Minor. Part 2. An annotated checklist of leuciscine fishes (Leuciscinae, Cyprinidae) of Turkey with descriptions of a new species and two new subspecies." volume="94" year="1997">Bogutskaya (1997)</bibRefCitation>
also supported this view (
<bibRefCitation author="Freyhof, J" journalOrPublisher="Ichthyological Exploration of Freshwaters" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" pagination="1 - 10" refId="B13" refString="Freyhof, J, Oezulug, M, 2014. Acanthobrama thisbeae, a new species of bream from southern Anatolia, Turkey (Teleostei: Cyprinidae). Ichthyological Exploration of Freshwaters 25 (1): 1 - 10" title="Acanthobrama thisbeae, a new species of bream from southern Anatolia, Turkey (Teleostei: Cyprinidae)." volume="25" year="2014">
Freyhof and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Özuluğ">Oezulug</normalizedToken>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Freyhof, J" journalOrPublisher="Ichthyological Exploration of Freshwaters" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" pagination="1 - 10" refId="B13" refString="Freyhof, J, Oezulug, M, 2014. Acanthobrama thisbeae, a new species of bream from southern Anatolia, Turkey (Teleostei: Cyprinidae). Ichthyological Exploration of Freshwaters 25 (1): 1 - 10" title="Acanthobrama thisbeae, a new species of bream from southern Anatolia, Turkey (Teleostei: Cyprinidae)." volume="25" year="2014">
Freyhof and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Özuluğ">Oezulug</normalizedToken>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
accepted 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. orontis" pageId="0" pageNumber="747" rank="species" species="orontis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="747">A. orontis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid although they did not find it in the Orontes River. The species, which was not observed in the fieldwork, might prefer the local area in the Orontes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
